newsitem.title: USA: FCOJ futures end up, seen rangebound before winter.
newsitem.headline: FCOJ futures end up, seen rangebound before winter.

text.p: NYCE frozen concentrated orange juice futures maintained their recent dull tone amid a dearth of news, balanced technicals, and a lack of interest from players, market sources said.
Support and resistance levels were unchanged at 97.50 and 102.50 cents a lb, respectively, basis the January contract.
The most-active January contract settled 0.60 cent a lb higher at 99.75, having ranged from 100.25 to 99.10. The back months finished 0.55 and 0.50 firmer.
Merrill Lynch analyst Judith Ganes said the market should maintain its current trading range until colder weather reaches the Florida citrus belt.
She also said the aggressive industry promotion of ready to serve orange juice from concentrate, could boost movement in the coming season, and help absorb the larger crop.
